title: Military jets escort Pakistan International Airlines flight into London Stansted after threat
text:
Military jets escort Pakistan International Airlines flight into London Stansted after threat Flight PK757 took off from Lahore Credit: Telegraph Reporters 7 February 2017 • 3:48pm 
A Pakistan International Airways flight from Lahore to Heathrow was diverted to Stansted on Tuesday, with police scrambled to meet it at the airport. 
Flight PK757 took off from Pakistan’s second largest city and landed at about 3pm. PIA flight from Lahore to London Heathrow diverted to Stansted airport over reports of a suspicious item on the plane — Flight Alerts ⚠ (@FlightAlerts777) February 7, 2017 
M ore to follow.
